  "time_ut": 1660544795,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0db7\u0dd6\u0dad\u0dba\u0dcf \u0d9c\u0dab\u0db1\u0dca \u0d8b\u0dc3\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dba\u0dd2:\u0d9c\u0ddc\u0dc0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca \u0db1\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dad\u0dca\u0dad\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The demon raises the numbers: the farmers are poor",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Farmers across the island are in a lot of trouble as they are unable to harvest due to the unexpected increase in threshing machine fees.",
        "The farmers are asking the government to provide some relief for the inconvenience they have to face.",
        "Farmers point out that although tillage cutting machines used to charge around 12,000 rupees for cutting an acre of stubble, it has now increased from 24,000 rupees to 25,000 rupees.",
        "Farmers also point out that they cannot afford to spend a lot of money to cut the crops that have barely been successful using fertilizers at high prices and there is a tendency for farmers to stay away from paddy cultivation.",
        "Regarding the unfair increase in paddy harvesting fees, Gampaha District Governor W.J. Satyananda said:",
        "Several filling stations have been identified in Gampaha district to provide fuel for machines for cutting and ploughing. Due to the release of fuel through agriculture officials and regional secretaries, the necessary measures will be discussed and taken urgently in the agriculture committee meeting which will be held tomorrow (16).",
        "The Governor also said that he will discuss with the owners of threshing machines as soon as possible about the fuel supply and the fees charged and find out whether it is possible to provide immediate relief to the farmers."
      ],
